        <h2 id="kd">Kraft Dinner</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 15 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 3</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Box of Kraft Dinner</td>
                    <td>1 Box</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Water</td>
                    <td>6 Cups</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Margarine</td>
                    <td>1/4 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>1/4 Cup</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Bring water to boil in medium saucepan. Add Macaroni; cook 7 to 8 min. or until tender, stirring occasionally.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Drain. (Do not rinse.) Return macaroni to pan.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Add margarine, milk and Cheese Sauce Mix; mix well.
</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="http://www.kraftrecipes.com/recipes/kraft-macaroni-cheese-dinner-56248.aspx">Kraft Dinner</a></em><br><br><a href="#BackTop">Back To Top</a><br><br></p>
    
    <h2 id="Cookie">Cookies</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 45 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 48</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Granulated Sugar</td>
                    <td>3/4 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Brown Sugar</td>
                    <td>3/4 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Margarine</td>
                    <td>1 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Vanilla</td>
                    <td>1 TSP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Egg</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>All-Purpose Flour</td>
                    <td>2 1/4 Cup</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Baking Soda</td>
                    <td>1 TSP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Salt</td>
                    <td>1/2 TSP</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Chopped Nuts</td>
                    <td>1 Cup</td>
                </tr><tr>
                    <td>Chocolate Chips</td>
                    <td>2 Cups</td>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Heat oven to 375-F
        <br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Mix sugars, butter, vanilla and egg in large bowl. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt (dough will be stiff). Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown (centers will be soft). Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet. Cool on wire rack.
</p>
        
    <p><em>Source: <a href="https://www.bettycrocker.com/recipes/ultimate-chocolate-chip-cookies/77c14e03-d8b0-4844-846d-f19304f61c57">Cookies</a></em><br><br><a href="#BackTop">Back To Top</a><br><br></p>
    
    <h2 id="Pizza">Pizza and *A certain cold drink*</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 15 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 4</li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Delissio Pizza</td>
                    <td>1 Box</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Cold *Certain Drink*</td>
                    <td>4 Cans/Bottles</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Summer day</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                
            </thead>
            <tbody>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Make sure *Certain Cold Drink* is cold, because nobody likes a warm pint.
        <br>
        <strong>Step 2:</strong> Put Pizza in Oven
        <br>
        <strong>Step 3:</strong> Cook Pizza for 15 minutes
        <br>
        <strong>Step 4:</strong> Sit outside and enjoy your *Certain Cold Drink* and pizza.
        <br><br>
        <strong>NOTE:</strong> THIS RECIPE ONLY WORKS IN THE SUMMER.<br><br><br>
        
        <a href="#BackTop">Back To Top</a>
</p>
        
    
